00:25:00,769 --> 00:25:05,412
So bringing back those two exterior space after we pivoted,

439
00:25:05,412 --> 00:25:08,515
we extended the model now and it's a full level

440
00:25:08,515 --> 00:25:12,398
in the game called Odd Spartacans.

441
00:25:12,398 --> 00:25:14,399
So I had to speed up the image here

442
00:25:14,399 --> 00:25:16,861
so you guys can see the entire level of the game.

443
00:25:16,861 --> 00:25:25,848
Here's the first interior space we built,

444
00:25:25,848 --> 00:25:28,490
concept art above and the game running below.

445
00:25:29,511 --> 00:25:31,412
With the new technique in Pipeline,

446
00:25:31,412 --> 00:25:33,173
we now have learnings to leverage

447
00:25:33,173 --> 00:25:34,654
any concept art style we want.

448
00:25:34,654 --> 00:25:38,696
Now that we successfully have the environment art style

449
00:25:38,696 --> 00:25:40,937
in Pipeline working in game,

450
00:25:40,937 --> 00:25:42,017
how do we design characters

451
00:25:42,017 --> 00:25:43,658
and scale the world of After Party?

452
00:25:43,658 --> 00:25:47,820
How do we make environment art look alive?

453
00:25:47,820 --> 00:25:56,384
How do we approach character modeling,

454
00:25:56,384 --> 00:25:58,305
texturing, rigging, and animation

455
00:25:58,305 --> 00:25:59,286
with a ton of characters?

456
00:26:00,777 --> 00:26:04,520
We wanted a variety of shapes and sizes for all of our main characters and NPCs.

457
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:11,885
Adam Hines wanted Satan to be twice his size and be the most prominent and interesting

458
00:26:11,885 --> 00:26:14,247
silhouette in the game.

459
00:26:14,247 --> 00:26:17,629
All of our characters had to be 3D and they were all modeled in Maya and ZBrush.

460
00:26:20,466 --> 00:26:22,187
So starting with our protagonist.

461
00:26:22,187 --> 00:26:25,009
So here's Milo's initial character designs.

462
00:26:25,009 --> 00:26:27,170
I went through a few changes.

463
00:26:27,170 --> 00:26:29,432
We started off with cardigans, trench coats,

464
00:26:29,432 --> 00:26:32,294
sporty jackets, Air Jordans, and jeans.

465
00:26:32,294 --> 00:26:35,576
Our characters' colors had to complement each other

466
00:26:35,576 --> 00:26:39,138
since they're gonna be together all the time.

467
00:26:39,138 --> 00:26:42,620
With Milo, we chose a simple, clean design

468
00:26:42,620 --> 00:26:46,403
with a yellow cardigan, jeans, and purple hair

469
00:26:46,403 --> 00:26:47,663
that echoed his personality.

470
00:26:50,652 --> 00:26:53,653
So Milo's backstory, he's an only child,

471
00:26:53,653 --> 00:26:56,614
intelligent and skated through college with ease.

472
00:26:56,614 --> 00:26:59,935
His fear of rejection stopped him from making new friends.

473
00:26:59,935 --> 00:27:01,996
So the choices we made for his designs

474
00:27:01,996 --> 00:27:04,037
were indicative of his personality.

475
00:27:05,235 --> 00:27:08,138
So you have purple hair, like I'm cool.

476
00:27:08,138 --> 00:27:10,341
Open collared shirt, I'm kind of up for anything.

